### 3.3 Core AI Pipeline — Text Simplification

The crown jewel of the backend. Here's the full pipeline:

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["Raw Text Input"] --> B["Cognitive Load Analysis<br/>(spaCy + textstat)"]
    B --> C{"Auto-Select<br/>Level 1/2/3"}
    C --> D["LLM Simplification<br/>(Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B)"]
    D --> E["Re-Analyze<br/>Simplified Text"]
    E --> F["Compute Reduction %"]
    F --> G["Return Structured JSON<br/>+ Impact Summary"]
```

#### Cognitive Load Scoring Formula — [cognitive_load.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/services/cognitive_load.py)

**Score Range:** 0 (easy) → 100 (hard), computed as a weighted sum:

| Factor | Weight | Metric | Source |
|---|---|---|---|
| Readability | 40% | `1 - (Flesch Reading Ease / 100)` | `textstat` |
| Sentence Length | 30% | `(avg_words_per_sentence - 5) / 30` | `spaCy` sentencizer |
| Complex Vocabulary | 30% | `difficult_words / total_words / 0.30` | `textstat.difficult_words()` |

**Final Score:** `100 × (0.4 × readability + 0.3 × sentence + 0.3 × vocabulary)` → clamped [0, 100]

This scoring engine also provides:
- **Sentence-level heatmap** — per-sentence cognitive load scores
- **Difficult word extraction** with character offsets (for UI highlighting)
- **Estimated reading time** (words / 200 WPM)

#### LLM Integration — [llm_client.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/services/llm_client.py)

- Uses **Groq API** (OpenAI-compatible interface) with **LLaMA 3.3 70B Versatile**
- Temperature: **0.3** (low variance for consistent simplification)
- Timeout: **15s**, max retries: **2**
- Returns structured JSON: `simplified_text`, `bullet_points`, `definitions`, `step_by_step_explanation`
- **Fallback logic**: if LLM fails → split sentences, truncate, return raw

#### IRT-Based Difficulty Detection — [simplification_engine.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/services/simplification_engine.py)

Runs **before simplification** to proactively tell the user if text needs simplifying:
- Maps Flesch-Kincaid Grade Level to **IRT theta scale**: `difficulty = (FK_grade - 6) / 3.0`
- Compares against user ability using **ZPD boundary** (should_simplify = difficulty > ability + 0.5)

