### 3.4 Adaptive Learning ML Engine — [ml/](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/ml)

This is the most technically impressive part of the project — **4 research-backed ML models** working together:

#### 🔬 Bayesian Knowledge Tracing (BKT) — [bkt_engine.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/ml/bkt_engine.py)
> *Reference: Corbett & Anderson (1994)*

Tracks **P(know)** for each skill (bd_confusion, pq_confusion, phonics, spelling, comprehension):
- **4 parameters**: P(init)=0.1, P(transit)=0.09, P(slip)=0.10, P(guess)=0.25
- Bayesian update: `P(know | obs) = P(obs | know) × P(know) / P(obs)`
- Learning transition: `P(know_new) = posterior + (1 - posterior) × P(transit)`
- **Mastery threshold**: P(know) ≥ 0.85

#### 📊 Item Response Theory (IRT) — [irt_scorer.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/ml/irt_scorer.py)
> *Reference: Lord (1952) — 1-Parameter Logistic / Rasch Model*

Estimates student **ability (theta)** on a [-3, +3] scale:
- `P(correct) = 1 / (1 + exp(-(ability - difficulty)))`
- Gradient-based ability update: `delta = correct - P(correct)`
- Maps ability to approximate grade level (0-12)

#### 📅 SM-2 Spaced Repetition — [sm2_scheduler.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/ml/sm2_scheduler.py)
> *Reference: Wozniak (1987) — SuperMemo Algorithm*

Schedules when to review each skill:
- Rep 0 → 1 day, Rep 1 → 6 days, Rep n → `interval × easiness_factor`
- Easiness factor updated per-answer quality (0-5 scale)
- Minimum easiness: 1.3 (accounts for dyslexia's higher forgetting rates)
- Due checking with human-readable labels ("Tomorrow", "In 3 days", etc.)

#### 🎯 Zone of Proximal Development (ZPD) — [zpd_flow.py](file:///e:/NR-main/backend/app/ml/zpd_flow.py)
> *Reference: Vygotsky (1978)*

Classifies exercise difficulty relative to student ability:
- **Too Easy**: ability > difficulty + 0.3 (boredom zone)
- **ZPD**: within ±0.3 theta units (optimal learning zone)
- **Too Hard**: difficulty > ability + 0.3 (frustration zone)
- **Recommendation**: target difficulty = ability + 0.15 (just challenging enough)

#### How They Work Together

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Student
