## 6. Unique Differentiators

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These are the things that make NeuroRead **stand out** from typical portfolio projects.

### 6.1 Research-Backed ML, Not Just "Uses AI"
Most projects call an LLM and call it "AI-powered." NeuroRead implements **4 published ML models** (BKT, IRT, SM-2, ZPD) from educational psychology research with proper citations. This demonstrates understanding of **learning science**, not just API calls.

### 6.2 Quantitative Cognitive Load Measurement
The weighted formula (Flesch + sentence length + vocabulary complexity) provides a **measurable, reproducible metric** — not a subjective rating. Before/after comparison with percentage reduction quantifies the actual impact of simplification.

### 6.3 Full Adaptive Loop
It's not a static app. The system adapts in real-time:
- **BKT** knows what the student knows
- **IRT** estimates their ability level
- **ZPD** keeps exercises in the optimal learning zone
- **SM-2** schedules reviews at the right time
This is how **Duolingo-class adaptive learning** works.

### 6.4 Clinical-Grade Reporting
The PDF clinical report export feature (via jsPDF) targets a real use case: parents and teachers need documentation for educational assessments and IEP meetings. This shows product thinking beyond technical demo.

### 6.5 Production Deployed & Environment-Aware
Not a localhost demo — full CI/CD pipeline with environment-managed API keys, CORS configuration, and separate frontend/backend deployment.

### 6.6 Genuine Accessibility, Not Token Effort
14+ adjustable accessibility parameters, 10 color overlays, OpenDyslexic font, reading rulers, chunk reading, TTS, speech-to-text input, keyboard shortcuts — this is **WCAG-informed** design for a population that genuinely needs it.

